         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/5/84 ¶  ¶ Let me hope, dear Mr Tepper, that you will  ¶ draw ¶   ¶ Drosera aphylla ¶  in bloom very accurately in this season. In my quarto volume  ¶ Plants of Victoria ¶  there is a detailed drawin...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">84.05.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply 12.5.84'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>7/5/84</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lassen Sie mich hoffen, lieber Herr Tepper, dass Sie <name key="Drosera%20aphylla">Drosera aphylla</name> recht genau in Blüthe z</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eichnen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> werden in dieser Jahreszeit. In meinem Quart. Bande, "plants of Victoria" ist eine ausführliche Zeichnung von Dros. Whittackeri, so dass Sie gute Stützpunkte für Vergleich im Zeichnen haben. Nach getrockneter Exemplare lässt sich die innere Structur der Blume nicht gut beschreiben.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Auch Früchte sollten sorgsam u reif gesammelt werden. Es wird sich dann bestimmt herausstellen, ob D. aphylla eine wirkliche entschieden characteristische Art sei oder nur eine abnorme Form.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hoffentlich haben Sie nun endlich die 9te Decade der Eucalyptographie erhalten.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-align: end; text-indent: -0.4929in; "
               xml:lang="en">7/5/84</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, dear Mr Tepper, that you will <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">draw</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Drosera%20aphylla">Drosera aphylla</name>
               </seg> in bloom very accurately in this season. In my quarto volume <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Plants of Victoria</seg> there is a detailed drawing of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Drosera%20whittackeri">Drosera whittackeri</name>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B79.06.04, p. 53.</p>
               </note> so that you have a good basis for comparison in drawing. The inner structure of the flower is not able to be properly described from dried specimens.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Also fruits should be collected carefully and ripe. It will then certainly become apparent whether <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. aphylla</seg> is a really distinctly characteristic species or only an abnormal form.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The specimen sent to M is at MEL 96925, and has Tepper's label 'Clarendon, 7.4.82 | grassy hillside in very dry soil, without any radical leaves, social | 618'. M's label is '<name key="Drosera%20aphylla">Drosera aphylla</name> FvM | Holds the same relat. to D. Whittackeri as D. squamosa to D. erythrorrhiza.' See Tepper (1892), p. 357, where he described the species as<seg style="font-style: italic; "> D. praefolia</seg>.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to O. Tepper, 26 April 1882 (in this edition as 82-04-26a), and M to O. Tepper, 17 May 1884.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is to be hoped you now have finally received the 9th decade of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptographia</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B84.04.04.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Drosera%20aphylla">Drosera aphylla</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Drosera%20whittackeri">Drosera whittackeri</name>
            </p>
         </div>
